r-intensive%20jobs%2C%20and%20low%20pay%20could%20be%20making%20it%20more%20difficult%20for%20hospitals%20and%20care%20facilities%20to%20attract%20employees%2C%20the%20report%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAverage%20wages%20for%20healthcare%20workers%20have%20increased%20overall%20since%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20but%20KFF%20said%20this%20could%20be%20because%20fewer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC8067982%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Elow-wage%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20workers%20are%20employed%20in%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC10266848%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2023%20National%20Institute%20of%20Health%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20inadequate%20pay%20is%20the%20most%20frequently%20cited%20reason%20employees%20give%20for%20burnout%20and%20leaving%20medicine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20slow%20gains%2C%20the%20Bank%20of%20America's%20report%20said%20it's%20a%20good%20sign%20that%20healthcare%20facilities%20appear%20to%20be%20hiring%20more%20full-time%20workers%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20finding%20that%20contract%20payments%20are%20easing%20indicates%20that%20firms%20may%20be%20under%20less%20pressure%20from%20labor%20shortages%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20could%20imply%20normalizing%20employment%20growth%20ahead.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20you%20a%20healthcare%20worker%20experiencing%20burnout%3F%20Are%20you%20a%20patient%20who%20has%20experienced%20long%20wait%20times%20because%20of%20hospital%20staffing%20shortages%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aallisonkelly%40insider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eallisonkelly%40insider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bus