0has%20pushed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Faverage-mortgage-interest-rate%5C%22%3Emortgage%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20up.%20This%20includes%20March's%20Consumer%20Price%20Index%20report%2C%20which%20showed%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-cpi-food-energy-gas-prices-consumer-price-index-2024-4%5C%22%3Eprices%20rose%203.5%25%20year%20over%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20month%2C%20a%20slight%20uptick%20from%20February's%203.2%25%20reading.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20could%20see%20mortgage%20rates%20start%20to%20trend%20down%20later%20this%20year%20if%20incoming%20data%20shows%20that%20inflation%20is%20coming%20down%20sustainably.%20But%20they'll%20probably%20remain%20elevated%20at%20least%20throughout%20the%20spring%20and%20summer%2C%20when%20homebuying%20activity%20is%20typically%20at%20its%20peak.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20rates%20trend%20higher%2C%20potential%20homebuyers%20are%20deciding%20whether%20to%20buy%20before%20rates%20rise%20even%20more%20or%20hold%20off%20in%20hopes%20of%20decreases%20later%20in%20the%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20Sam%20Khater%2C%20Freddie%20Mac's%20chief%20economist%2C%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffreddiemac.gcs-web.com%2Fnews-releases%2Fnews-release-details%2Fmortgage-rates-exceed-7-percent-first-time-year%5C%22%3Epress%20release%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BLast%20week%2C%20purchase%20applications%20rose%20modestly%2C%20but%20it%20remains%20unclear%20how%20many%20homebuyers%20can%20withstand%20increasing%20rates%20in%20the%20future.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20month%2C%20existing-home%20sales%20fell%204.3%25%20from%20February%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nar.realtor%2Fnewsroom%2Fexisting-home-sales-descended-4-3-in-march%5C%22%3ENational%20Association%20of%20Realtors%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20were%20also%20down%203.7%25%20year%20over%20year.%20While%20more%20buyers%20may%20start%20shopping%20for%20homes%20as%20the%20weather%20warms%20up%2C%20high%20rates%20will%20continue%20to%20price%20many%20people%20out%20of%20the%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMortgage%20Rates%20Today%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Ch2%3EMortgage%20Refinance%20Rates%20Today%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Ch3%3EMortgage%20Calculator%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EUse%20our%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20data-analytics-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%2240%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgage-calculator%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efree%20mortgage%20calculator%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20see%20how%20today's%20mortgage%20rates%20will%20affect%20your%20monthly%20and%20long-term%20payments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20plugging%20in%20different%20term%20lengths%20and%20interest%20rates%2C%20you'll%20see%20how%20your%20monthly%20payment%20could%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E30-Year%20Fixed%20Mortgage%20Rates%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20average%2030-year%20fixed%20mortgage%20rate%20was%207.10%25%20this%20week%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.freddiemac.com%2Fpmms%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFreddie%20Mac%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20is%2022%20basis%20points%20higher%20than%20it%20was%20the%20week%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2030-year%20fixed-rate%20mortgage%20is%20the%20most%20common%20type%20of%20home%20loan.%20With%20this%20type%20of%20mortgage%2C%20you'll%20pay%20back%20what%20you%20borrowed%20over%2030%20years%2C%20and%20your%20interest%20rate%20won't%20change%20for%20the%20life%20of%20the%20loan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lengthy%2030-year%20term%20allows%20you%20to%20spread%20out%20your%20payments%20over%20a%20long%20period%20of%20time%2C%20meaning%20you%20can%20keep%20your%20monthly%20payments%20lower%20and%20more%20manageable.%20The%20trade-off%20is%20that%20you'll%20have%20a%20higher%20rate%20than%20you%20would%20with%20shorter%20terms%20or%20adjustable%20rates.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E15-Year%20Fixed%20Mortgage%20Rates%